co.cask.cdap.api.dataset

Interface DatasetDefinition<D extends Dataset,A extends DatasetAdmin>

  • Type Parameters:
    D - defines data operations that can be performed on this dataset instance
    A - defines administrative operations that can be performed on this dataset instance
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    AbstractDatasetDefinition, CompositeDatasetDefinition, CounterTimeseriesTableDefinition, IndexedObjectStoreDefinition, IndexedTableDefinition, KeyValueTableDefinition, TimeseriesTableDefinition

    @Beta
public interface DatasetDefinition<D extends Dataset,A extends DatasetAdmin>
    Defines named dataset type implementation. The dataset implementation defines:
    • a way to configure new dataset instance by using configure(String, DatasetProperties) method
    • a way to perform administrative operations on the dataset instance (e.g. create, drop etc.) by providing implementation of DatasetAdmin via getAdmin(DatasetContext, DatasetSpecification, ClassLoader) method
    • a way to perform operations to manipulate data of the dataset instance (e.g. read, write etc.) by providing implementation of Dataset via getDataset(DatasetContext, DatasetSpecification, Map, ClassLoader) method

      • configure

        DatasetSpecification configure(String instanceName,
                             DatasetProperties properties)
        Configures new instance of the dataset.
        Parameters:
        instanceName - name of the instance
        properties - instance configuration properties
        Returns:
        instance of DatasetSpecification that fully describes dataset instance. The DatasetSpecification can be used to create DatasetAdmin and Dataset to perform administrative and data operations respectively, see getAdmin(DatasetContext, DatasetSpecification, ClassLoader) and getDataset(DatasetContext, DatasetSpecification, Map, ClassLoader).

      • getDataset

        D getDataset(DatasetContext datasetContext,
           DatasetSpecification spec,
           Map<String,String> arguments,
           ClassLoader classLoader)
                             throws IOException
        Provides dataset to be used to perform data operations on the dataset instance data defined by passed DatasetSpecification and the given arguments.
        Parameters:
        datasetContext - context for the dataset
        spec - specification of the dataset instance.
        arguments - arguments for this instance of the dataset. Should not be null - provide an empty map for no arguments.
        classLoader - classloader to use when executing dataset operations
        Returns:
        dataset to perform object operations
        Throws:
        IOException
